				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "This new model will have the classes and methods that are currently defined in the running Smalltalk image. You can get a model class object by using either the {{gtMethod:RBNamespace>>#classFor:}} or {{gtMethod:RBNamespace>>#classNamed:}} method. The former takes a class from the Smalltalk image and the latter takes a name of a class. These return a model class that is of the {{gtClass:RBAbstractClass}} type (likely it will be a {{gtClass:RBClass}} or a {{gtClass:RBMetaclass}}). "
			},
			{
				"__type" : "pharoSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [ ]
