				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "To add a method or recompile a method in a class, use the {{gtMethod:RBAbstractClass>>compile:}} or the {{gtMethod:RBAbstractClass>>compile:classified:}} methods.  The first argument of both of these methods is a string that represents the method's source that is to be compiled. For the second method, you can specify a protocol that the method should be categorized under. The protocol is a symbol. If you want to remove a method, you can use the {{gtMethod:RBAbstractClass>>#removeMethod:}} method. The argument to the method is a symbol of the name of the method to be removed."
			},
